## 2. LARAVEL ARCHITECTURE & BEST PRACTICES

### Project Structure
**Recommendation**: Use **Repository Pattern** for this e-commerce project
- Repositories provide clean separation between data access and business logic
- Easier to switch database implementations if needed
- Ideal for complex queries (filters, searches, sorting)

```
app/
├── Models/
│   ├── Product.php
│   ├── Category.php
│   ├── Order.php
│   ├── User.php
│   └── ...
├── Repositories/
│   ├── Contracts/
│   │   ├── ProductRepositoryInterface.php
│   │   └── OrderRepositoryInterface.php
│   ├── ProductRepository.php
│   ├── OrderRepository.php
│   └── ...
├── Services/
│   ├── ProductService.php
│   ├── OrderService.php
│   └── SitemapService.php
├── Http/
│   ├── Controllers/
│   │   ├── ProductController.php
│   │   ├── Admin/
│   │   │   ├── ProductController.php
│   │   │   ├── OrderController.php
│   │   │   ├── CategoryController.php
│   │   │   └── DashboardController.php
│   │   └── ...
│   └── Requests/
│       ├── StoreProductRequest.php
│       └── ...
├── Traits/
│   └── HasSeoMetadata.php
└── Helpers/
    └── SeoHelper.php
```

### Code Style
- Use **type hints** for all methods
- Use **strict types** at the top of files: `declare(strict_types=1);`
- Follow **PSR-12** coding standards
- Use meaningful variable and method names
- Document complex business logic with comments

### Model Relationships
```php
// Product Model
public function category() { return $this->belongsTo(Category::class); }
public function images() { return $this->hasMany(ProductImage::class); }
public function reviews() { return $this->hasMany(Review::class); }
public function orderItems() { return $this->hasMany(OrderItem::class); }

// Category Model
public function products() { return $this->hasMany(Product::class); }
public function children() { return $this->hasMany(Category::class, 'parent_id'); }
public function parent() { return $this->belongsTo(Category::class, 'parent_id'); }

// Order Model
public function items() { return $this->hasMany(OrderItem::class); }
public function user() { return $this->belongsTo(User::class); }
```

### Caching Strategy
```php
// Cache product listings
$products = Cache::remember('products.all', 3600, function () {
    return Product::with('category', 'images')->where('is_active', true)->get();
});

// Clear cache when products updated
Product::created(fn($product) => Cache::flush('products.*'));
```

