## 5. CLIENT-SIDE (FRONTEND) GUIDELINES

### Technology Stack
- **Tailwind CSS**: CDN version (not npm build)
- **Alpine.js**: For interactivity without page reload
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach

### Tailwind CDN Setup
```html
<!-- In base layout -->
<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
<script defer src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/alpinejs@3.x.x/dist/cdn.min.js"></script>
```

### Mobile-First Design Principles
- **Breakpoints Priority**: `mobile → tablet → desktop`
- **Touch-friendly**: Minimum 44px tap targets
- **Performance**: Lazy load images, minimal CSS
- **Images**: Use `srcset` for responsive images
- **Forms**: Large input fields, clear labels

### Image Optimization
```blade
<!-- Use picture element with srcset -->
<picture>
    <source media="(min-width: 768px)" srcset="{{ asset('storage/'.$product->image_url) }}">
    <img src="{{ asset('storage/'.$product->image_mobile) }}" alt="{{ $product->name }}">
</picture>

<!-- Or use responsive classes -->
<img class="w-full md:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3" src="{{ asset('storage/'.$product->image_url) }}" alt="{{ $product->name }}">
```

### Product Listing Page
```html
<!-- Grid with mobile responsiveness -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
    @foreach($products as $product)
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow">
            <!-- Image -->
            <img src="{{ asset('storage/'.$product->image_url) }}" 
                 alt="{{ $product->name }}"
                 loading="lazy"
                 class="w-full h-48 object-cover">
            
            <!-- Content -->
            <div class="p-3">
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">{{ $product->name }}</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">{{ $product->brand }}</p>
                <p class="text-lg font-bold text-green-600 mt-2">Rs. {{ $product->price }}</p>
                <button class="w-full bg-blue-600 text-white py-2 rounded mt-2 text-sm">
                    Add to Cart
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
    @endforeach
</div>
```

### Alpine.js for Interactivity
```blade
<!-- Product filter with Alpine -->
<div x-data="{ 
    minPrice: 0, 
    maxPrice: 50000,
    category: '',
    brand: ''
}">
    <input type="range" x-model="minPrice" class="w-full">
    <input type="range" x-model="maxPrice" class="w-full">
    <button @click="filterProducts()">Filter</button>
</div>

<!-- Cart counter -->
<span x-text="cartCount" class="bg-red-500 text-white rounded-full px-2">0</span>
```

