## 10. IMPORTANT REMINDERS

✅ **DO**:
- Use `with()` to eager load relationships
- Validate all user input with Form Requests
- Use pagination for large datasets
- Index foreign keys and frequently queried columns
- Implement SEO tags on every product/category page
- Cache expensive queries
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use Laravel conventions (naming, structure)

❌ **DON'T**:
- Create unnecessary database indexes
- Use `all()` without pagination
- Load relationships in loops
- Hardcode SEO meta tags
- Skip input validation
- Forget to add alt text to images
- Use outdated Laravel patterns

